## 6. Inter-Agent Communication Design

### Message Schema (standardised)
```python
{
    "sender": "research_agent",
    "recipient": "writer_agent",
    "task_id": "uuid-1234",
    "message_type": "task_result",
    "content": "Here are the 5 key findings from the research...",
    "metadata": {
        "sources": ["url1", "url2"],
        "confidence": 0.87,
        "timestamp": "2025-03-07T10:30:00Z"
    }
}
```

### Conversation Patterns
- **Ordered (sequential)**: Each agent processes in turn — deterministic, easier to debug
- **Unordered (asynchronous)**: Agents respond when ready — faster, harder to coordinate
- **Group chat**: All agents see all messages — enables emergent coordination

---

## 7. MAS Failure Modes and Mitigations

| Failure Mode | Mitigation |
|-------------|------------|
| Hallucination cascade | Each agent validates previous agent's output |
| Infinite loops | Max iteration limits + convergence checks |
| Context overflow | Summarise intermediate results between agents |
| Agent conflict | Arbitration agent or majority voting |
| Capability mismatch | Capability registry + routing logic |
| Lack of observability | Structured logging of all inter-agent messages |

